\sum h_nx^n=\overbrace{(1+x^2+x^4+\cdots)}^\text{apples}\cdot\overbrace{(1+x+x^2)}^\text{oranges}\cdot\overbrace{(1+x^3+x^6+\cdots)}^\text{bananas}\cdot\overbrace{(1+x)}^\text{pears}.
\sum h_nx^n=\frac{1}{1-x^2}\cdot(1+x+x^2)\cdot\frac{1}{1-x^3}\cdot(1+x) = \frac{1}{(1-x)^2}.
